  "title": "Courtesy in the Starlight Gardens",
  "summary": "In the terraced Starlight Gardens cafe, the recovering New Republic Ambassador Ambrosia takes a break from shopping when the cool, former-Imperial broker Zeak Oppenhiemer makes a careful covert contact, opening a frank discussion about the looming crisis on Caspar. They are joined by the marine Amaya Halos, who once helped pull Ambrosia from Imperial captivity, and the three dissect Aldus Thel's ambitions to win a PR victory and cut the Republic's supply line by controlling Caspar's weapons trade. Zeak warns of plans to use a CSA strike group of Star Destroyers for the aid flotilla, while Ambrosia admits to bankrolling the pirates harassing Imperial shipments and bristles at any suggestion of treating her smuggler assets as expendable pawns. They reach an understanding: Ambrosia will call off her people and Zeak will assure the Direx board the Republic won't interfere with humanitarian deliveries. The conversation closes with bitter reflections on Caspar's ruin and Halos's curt mention of Alderaan, the scene pausing before its wrap-up.",
